91, \"rank\": 8.764963111993355e-11, \"text\": \"American woman\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \">> Texas high school athletes competing in the 2024 Paris Olympics  To further drive home the rarity, even the act of qualifying in both events was a first for the U.S. women.\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 291, \"end\": 296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Longhorns\", \"score\": 0.9955201091352676, \"rank\": 0.004412466665719803, \"text\": \"Texas\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Longhorns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Longhorns\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 23-year-old Grand Prairie native won bronze in the triple and long jump in Paris this month.\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 544, \"end\": 549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999997026744027, \"rank\": 2.9732572905623954e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She secured the bronze in the long jump on Saturday, becoming Team USA's first medalist in the event on the women's side.\", \"from\": 563, \"to\": 684, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 625, \"end\": 633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9974484003418124, \"rank\": 0.0025580073702381172, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Thursday, she took bronze in the triple jump with a 14.67 meter jump, which came in ahead of Jamaica's Shanieka Ricketts' (14.87) and Dominica's Thea LaFond (15.02).\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 854, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 782, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9854833545589389, \"rank\": 0.014730140076053482, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominica\", \"score\": 0.997556930906949, \"rank\": 0.0024490522970795543, \"text\": \"Dominica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominica\"}, {\"begin\": 834, \"end\": 845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thea_LaFond\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thea LaFond\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thea_LaFond\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thea_LaFond\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moore won seven NCAA Championships total across her stints at Georgia and Florida.\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 918, \"end\": 925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"score\": 0.9774403620647313, \"rank\": 0.013100725999521425, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\"}, {\"begin\": 930, \"end\": 937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida_Gators\", \"score\": 0.9999972877240401, \"rank\": 1.9582577331948877e-06, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida_Gators\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida_Gators\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those who witnessed her on the high school stage saw the early makings of an all-time career.\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 1033, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She won 5A state championships in the long and triple jumps all four of her years from 2016-19.\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1130, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a sophomore, she was the lead-off runner in a state runner-up 4x100 team, and went on to place seventh at New Balance Outdoor Nationals in the event.\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1284, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1241, \"end\": 1252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Balance\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New Balance\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Balance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Balance\"}, {\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_Nationals\", \"score\": 0.9998758611502016, \"rank\": 0.00012240730017553357, \"text\": \"Nationals\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_Nationals\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_Nationals\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After her senior season, she was named Gatorade National Girls Track and Field Athlete of the Year.\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1385, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She left college with the NCAA triple jump record, as well as indoor long jump and triple jump records.\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1490, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1413, \"end\": 1417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999988416159228, \"rank\": 1.1582276421435656e-06, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"-- Andy Buhler | andy@scorebooklive.com |@sblivetx  Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1570, \"entities\": 